Clear- calm- 80 F- water temp: 78 F- no rain the past week- slight algae bloom.
Sunny- SE winds at 10-15 mph- 80 F- pH: 7.8- MPA: 26 ppm.
Clear- sunny 60 F- pH 7.8- S wind 10-12 mph- MPA = 28 parts per million.
Partly cloudy- 52 F- SE wind 10-15 mph.
Cool and overcast- breeze 5-7 mph- air temp cool at 50 degrees.
Bright sunny beautiful day- WNW wind at 5-7 mph- air temp 82 degrees.
Partly cloudy- SW winds 15-18 mph- pH is 7.8- air temp is 74 degrees.
Southwest wind 5-7 mph- pH is 7.6- partly cloudy @ 70 degrees.  MPA is 28  parts per million.
SE wind 10-15 mph- air temp is 72 degrees- partly cloudy- 1" of rain in the past 24 hours.
N wind @ 10 mph- air temp is 74 degrees- clear and sunny- .75" of rain in the last 24 hours.  pH is 7.4- MPA is 32 parts per million.
Partly cloudy- air temp 58- SE breeze 5-7 mph.
Sunny- air temp 70- NW wind 10-15 mph- pH 7.6- MPA 30 parts per million.
Partly cloudy- SW wind 10 mph- air temp 74- pH 7.8- MPA 29 parts per million.
Partly sunny- NW wind 5-7 mph- air temp 78.
Winds SW @ 10-20 mph- partly cloudy- 48 degree air- 52 degree water.
Southwest wind 10-15 mph- Bluegills biting good!- Bluegills tasting good!
Partly cloudy- air 76 degrees- SW wind 5-10 mph.
Overcast- air temp. 78 degrees- SE wind 0-5 mph.
Hazy and warm- 80 degrees- SW breeze- 10 mph- Thermocline 19'-22'.
SE wind @ 15-20 mph- hazy- warm- 82 degrees- nicest day of the summer.
Partly cloudy. 65 degrees. SE wind 10-15 mph.
Partly cloudy. 72 degrees.  West wind 10-15 mph.
Partly cloudy - 80 degrees. SW breeze - 15 mph.  Large amounts of bushy pondweed floating on surface.
Overcast- 72 degrees- S wind 10-20 mph.  Bushy pondweed all blew into north end of lake.
Partly cloudy-80 degrees- south breeze 5 mph- too many jet skis.
Southwest wind 15-20 mph- choppy- hot 92 degrees F- no rain past 24 hours.
Warm 87 degrees- clear- SE breeze 5 mph- 1" rain past 24 hours.
SE wind 15-20 mph- 76 degrees- partly cloudy.
Calm- humid- 82 degrees F- partly cloudy- 3" rain past 24 hours.
Partly cloudy- 65 degrees- SW breeze 5 mph.  Opening of duck season.  Time for cheese and crackers.
Cold=36 degrees- overcast- west wind 15 mph.
Clear to partly cloudy.  Ice off 4/12/1996. 50 degrees in the air and 45 degrees in the water.  West wind 15 mph.
Cool A.M.-40 degrees- warm P.M.-75 degrees- slight NE breeze 10-15 mph.  Diatom bloom.
Hot 90 degrees air- unusual- extreme diatom bloom- slight breeze SE 5 mph.
Air 78 degrees F- water 80 degrees F- NW breeze 5 mph. clear skies!  Good friends!  Good fishing!  Great beer! (Dip-in) .
Air 86 degrees- water 80 degrees- SW breeze 5-10- clear- sunny- MPA-27- pH-8.2- slight blue-green algae bloom.
Partly cloudy- 78 degrees air- SW breeze 5 mph- fishing slow- water-skiing fast- (no jet skis sign).
Overcast- SE wind- humid- 80 degrees F- 5-10 mph. everyone is happy!  No jet skis!
Warm-78 degrees.  SE wind 5-10 mph.  No rain past week.  Partly cloudy.
Opening of duck season-went trout fishing instead.  Partly cloudy- 62 degrees- easterly winds 10-15.
Partly cloudy- 56 degrees.  No rain past week- diatom pulse last week in April.
Clear 81 degrees. N wind 10 mph.  Mostly fisherman- no skiers- plan to form Assoc. this year.
Air temp. 86 degrees. partly cloudy- 3" rain past few days- SW breeze- 5 mph.
Air = 82 degrees. 1/4" rain past 2 days- partly sunny- SW breeze 10 mph.
Air = 72 degrees. cool last 3 days- overcast- S breeze 10 mph.
Bluebird day.  Clear skies and 56 degrees.  Light easterly breeze.  Rain gauge reading from 10/9/97 to 10/16/97=.56 inches. pH=7.8 and MPA alkalinity = 27 parts per million.
Air temp 70 F- partly cloudy- mallards + wood ducks about- loons back- great spring.
Air temp 68 F- partly cloudy- NW wind 5-10 mph- pH 7.6- MPA 27- water temp 70 F / 21 C- 9.17" rain since April 4.
Air temp 89 F- SW wind 10-15 mph- overcast- pH 7.4- MPA 28- water temp.
Air temp 78 F- west wind 15-25 mph- clear sky- beautiful day!  Second brood mallards about-  MPA 29-  pH 7.2.
Air 56 F.  NW wind 15-20 mph.  Partly cloudy.  1 1/2" rain past week.  MPA 32.  pH 7.4.
Air 50 F. Calm clear beautiful day!  Ducks- geese- fish- deer- the land abounds with game!  We shall claim it for the king!!
Overcast- windy- and southwest wind at 5-10 mph.  Looks like a dry year.
Warm at 82 degrees- beautiful summer day with a southwest wind at 10-15 mph.  Finally at the cabin.
Overcast- northwest wind at 5-10 mph- lake is getting lower- and no rain to amount to anything.  Night of the 26th there was 3" of rain but did not help the lake!
Partly cloudy with a southeast breeze at 0-5 mph.  Nice day in the world!
Overcast- cool- southwest wind at 5-10 mph- and some leaves turning.  Back in town.
Water level is 24" lower than this spring.  I'll have to bring my own water to fish in!
Water level is lowest since 1984.  No rain- a sunny day.
Last observation for the year.  Partly cloudy and cold at 32 degrees with a southeast wind at 15 mph.  When fish swim away they leave a cloud of dust!!  That is how dry!!!
partly cloudy- SW breeze 5-10 mph- Happy Spring-

column1: Ducks- deer- eagles- Winter Survival at its best!

column2: Yea + Verily- the flowers bloom(er or Blummer)  Good rain- lake level up- good bluegills.
Water levels up from last year (1 ft) Sunny 75-

column1: Cabins open and in use Oh Boy!

column2: Hot + Humid - into the 90's this wee
Happy 4th- the lake is beautiful at 5:30am- Calm-

column1: flat and a few loons-me included

column2: Snow is gone but it is still winter! Air temp was

column1: 28.0F this AM.  Back to the mittens- Sorels and nose warmers.

column2: The popple pollen is so thick on the lake surface that it looks like snow or ice. Air temp is 85F. Thank goodness it is not winter- HAPPY SUMMER!!!
4.28" of rain past 24 hours. Lake is FULL! Dock is

column1: under water but the ducks are happy. Air temp 82- calm winds- high thin clouds. "AINT SUMMER GRAND !"

column2: Air temp 81F- partly cloudy- E wind 5-10 mph- 16" rain this

column1: summer. Ah summer- wish we had it in the winter!

column2: Air temp 80f- clear and calm. A beautiful summer day- A

column1: good memory day!

column2: Air temp 68f Fall is on its way.   This was a wet summer.  The trees around the lake are donning their fall colors preparing for the last dance of the year.  I know we will be invited. Joy to the world!
Cool Fall day.  Swans passing through.  Few ducks left.  The dance is almost over.  Have a good winter!
Spring has been great! Air 68-pptly cldy.
Warm water temps- 76F Grandkids having a

column1: great time!

column2: Lt rain- The 4th was a BANG !
Very little rain. The lake is still high but        I

column1: belive it is in a 15-18 year cycle of high and lows which my records
indicate.

column2: The long hot summer!That could be the name of a

column1: song...... No rain past month. Lake still high but dropping slightly.

column2: The drought continues. Lake still has water but when I

column1: go stream fishing- I have to take my own water! Glad to hear Dan Ryan
retired. He was a good representitive of the D N R .He will be missed.
Fall is here!

column2: Great day-80 degrees-calm- colorful-blue sky and if I

column1: had not looked at the date- I would think it was July! What a day to end
my data collection for the year.Talk to you in the spring :)-:)-:)!

column2: Finally-a warm day this month!The Maples are turning and the ducks are looking to the south .Fall is nigh upon us.
Great Spring day! I believe I will stay here for a while! The rest of summer!
Been cold and rainy last few days- still a good spring!
sunny with high puffy clouds- surface temp 81F- I wonder what the rest of the world is doing
Overcast but still great! Air 86F- lake level normal- Loons are happy!
water level seem to be receding- still a great summer.
water down- seem as if 1984 all over again
the lowest since 1984- no rain since June 26
heavy rains brought lake levels up to spring levels
so far lake looks good going into fall-winter. GREAT SUMMER C.U. next year.
Took a 55 alive class- good for seniors!
Memorial Day- fly the flag for the good old USA!!!
No special day- fly the flag anyway! Day! Day!
Grandkids with me today- start them young!!!
SUmmer has been dry. Had 2 northern and several bass at the door asking for a cup of water.
water getting lower each day. About the same as 1984. 16" lower than spring
Without offence to anyone- Indian summer is here!!!
Great fall- colors are great and fish are biting :)
unable to obtain fall H2O sample- Oh well- there's always next year!
Ice went out on the 23 of april- late this year. It usually leaves closer to April 12.I have documented ice-out dates since 1961.
Water level is up a few inches from last fall. Hopefully we will get more rain to help it along. It was down about 24 inches going into winter.
Nice clear day on Bass lake Not many boats seen this year- gas prices may have an affect on this. I'll keep you posted on this.
Beautiful day! Loons-ducks-deer and a bear. It seems that overall -the boaters and fishermen have been fewer this year. THATS OK WITH ME!!!!!

Great day in the morning! 82degrees with a light breeze from the NE. Have had several bunches of mallards grow up here this summer and they are now learning to fly. What a bunch of comedy on a beautiful day!
Cloudy and cool today.Air temp is around 58-60 degrees with a NW wind 10-15 mph.Rained about 3/4 inch in the past 24 hours. Hey! It's a great fall !
Nice day. Water level is LOW-LOW-LOW. please send more !!!
Water level is 4 inches lower than ice out. Overall lake level is 26 inches below ohm. The summer visitors will have to bring thier own water when they come up this year!

column1: Partly cloudy.62 degrees F-So wind 5-10 mph. Nice Day.....

column2: Lake level down11 inches since the first week in May.
Cool spring and now into the summer.Slow growing time for everything in this part of the state.
Beautiful summer day! Large puffy cloudsand no one on the lake except us natives. Lots of duck broods this year and they are littering my docks with used food!
Partly cloudy-west wind 5-1`0 mph and another cool september day.I ask - Where is just a little global warming
Still a lack of rain. If this continues- The trees around the lake will be happy to have the dogfish come onto the shorline for a visit.
Light rain past 24 hours. The water is still low. The catfish will be in the trees before long.
Beautiful summer AM. Calm-cool 48f at 7.00 AM  Lake level is 30-31 inches fow measured ffom the OHWM.Still good fishing tho!
beautiful fall day. light sw breeze and a partly cloudy sky. air temp is 80f. makes me glad that i am not sitting behind some cramped dnr desk wherever it may be.
Great day for a birthday and a boat ride.
Bass lake is 36 inches low at this time. The rain we have had this spring did not help. All tourests should bring thier own water to fish in!

column1: Cloudy-humid day. 72 degrees.

column2: not much to say.Happy birthday Christian!
Too many people today! I like the solitude of a quiet lake. I suppose share and share alike.Am I turning into a groutch
Thought i would try a different time of the day.
Happy 49th anniversary to me and my love!
Beatiful cool mourning after several hot humid days. Air temp is 70 and the water temp is 78.6. Partly cloudy with nw wind 8-10 mph. Great Day In the AM!
Looks like the start of a great fall. Moved back to town but visit the lake daily.

column1: Air temp 52
lake temp 66

column2: Cold spring so far! Ice went out on april 12
If the weather stays this cold the fish will have to spawn with gloves and scarves on.
Partly cloudy and finally warm. The bluegills are finally making reservations for spawning beds.
Its a beautiful day in the neighborhood!
partly cloudy and mild. great fall for fishing.
Nice day. the fall colors have been outstanding. Favorite time of the year.
unsettled weather pattern this week. Lake level about 32-36 inches low
last time this year. I thought the lake would regain some of its water but no such luck. maybe next year.
Warm spring . Good rain that has caused the lake to rise 3-4 inches. Hope it lasts!
Cloudy and mild. Very few fisherpeople on the lake so far this year.
Great spring so far.Not many lake people yet. Did I ofend them somehow last year
Not much for fireworks last night. Weather great for the last few weeks.They're back !
This is the first time I have been able to collect water samples. No D.O. tho.
Not too dry around here so far this summer. I had better watch what I say tho!
Overcast lite breeze from the SE
Still no significant rain. I knew as soon as i said anything- ........What an ego!
overcast-sw wind-choppy surface. Grandson helped-great partner.
partly cldy-SW breeze- walleye chop- if we had walleyes.
Summer is going too fast! Air temp 80-H2O-79
Been having more rain .I have had to raise the docks at least 6 inches!.
Humid day.Light rain last PM.Air temp 82- Water temp- 79
Lake is finally FULL after 6 years of extremely low water levels!

column1: See you next year if all goes well.

column2: Nice day. No jet skis- water skiersor anyone other than me on the lake. Air temp is 77- water is 77 and that is my age.An omen here- perhaps! Sent chems in today also.
Trying it a little early today.Partly cloudy and a welcome cool down. Hint of fall :)
Another nice fall day. Last day trout fishing. Had a great trout season and plan to have many more..
Fall- favorite time of the year. Spring- winter and summer are great also!
Last submit of the year. Hope to see you on the CLMN next year.
checking water clarity prior to the July 4th holiday. Nice summer day.
Same Secchi reading as before the holiday.
Warm-muggy -so far a very warm summer. GREAT!!!
beautiful day 78 degrees and mild and loons.
Great Sept day! I hope the entire fall is this way!!!!
Overcast- breezy -a grey fall day. Nice to be on the water!
Last observation for the year. Lots of fun.Grandkids can carry this on if I can't.See you next spring.
Took this after the 4th to see how boat traffic would affect the clarity
last check of the year. Had a great time. C U next spring.
End of season. See you next year.
warm-79 degrees-clear and calm. Great weekend weather.
Last secchi reading of the season. See you next spring.
Water samples on this date also.
